&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Chemotherapy Day Case and Oncology Outpatients&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 Per Week.    &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band  7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated Senior Sister to lead the team in Chemotherapy Day Case and Oncology Outpatients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fal is a busy Chemotherapy Day Case Unit who provide care for patients with Oncology conditions.  We treat patients with a range of complex therapeutic interventions including Immunotherapies, Blood transfusions, Chemotherapy and other supportive infusions. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oncology Outpatient Department supports consultant led oncology and haematology clinics. Pre-interventional talks are held with patient to discuss treatment options for new cancer diagnoses.  These talks are held in the department and some treatments are delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide Clinical Nurse Management, Clinical Leadership &amp; expertise in all aspects of service delivery and have responsibility for the department budget. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have recent relevant experience in a leadership capacity in Oncology at Band 6. Have good clinical skills &amp; knowledge in all aspects of Chemotherapy delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Matron Sharon Raymond email your expression of interest to  Sharon.raymond@nhs.net For further information bleep 81116 or extension 32492.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
